---
import CodeIcon from '../components/CodeIcon.astro'
import TimelineIcon from '../components/TimelineIcon.astro'
import ArchitectureIcon from '../components/ArchitectureIcon.astro'
import BusinessIcon from '../components/BusinessIcon.astro'

import Header from '../components/header.astro'
import PageHead from '../components/PageHead.astro'
import BoxVisual from '../components/BoxVisual.astro'
// Welcome to Astro! Everything between these triple-dash code fences
// is your "component frontmatter". It never runs in the browser.
console.log('This runs in your terminal, not the browser!');
---
<!-- Below is your "component template." It's just HTML, but with
     some magic sprinkled in to help you build great templates. -->
<html>
  <head>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Rubik&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header/>
    <PageHead>
      <h1>Getting started</h1>
    </PageHead>
    <div class="content">   
      <p>I build UIs for people trying to get things done.</p>
      <p>With primary experience building enterprise web UIs with React, my goal help people accomplish their tasks by crafting high quality tools that they can rely on.</p>

<!--      <div class="selling-point"><CodeIcon class="icon"/><span>Software Engineering</span></div>
      <div class="selling-point"><TimelineIcon class="icon"/><span>Project Manager</span></div>
      <div class="selling-point"><ArchitectureIcon class="icon"/><span>Architecture</span></div>
      <div class="selling-point"><BusinessIcon class="icon"/><span>Business Value</span></div>
 --> 

      <div class="graphic">
        <div class="discipline design">Design</div> 
        <div class="discipline product">Product</div> 
        <div class="discipline engineer">Engineering</div> 
        <svg viewbox="0 0 100 100" height="100" width="100">
            <polygon points="50 15, 100 100, 0 100" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="2"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p>UI Engineering is optimally positioned as the player who can collaborate effectively across all 3 disciplines of the software product delivery system.</p>
      <BoxVisual/>

      <p>Preview some thoughts on the following</p>
      <div class="thoughts"><a href="/thoughts/scaling">Scaling</a><a href="/thoughts/abstraction">Abstraction</a><a href="/thoughts/testing">Testing</a></div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
<style>
  body {
    --color1: #434E5F;
    --color2: #536C98;
    --color3: #2F7BE3;
    --color4: #62B0F4;
    --color5: #ADB1C5;

    --background: var(--color1);
    --text-primary: #FFFFFF;
    --text-subtle: var(--color5);
    --border: var(--color4);
    --action-primary: var(--color3);
    --background-alt: var(--color2);

    background: var(--color1);
    font-family: 'Rubik', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  :root {
    font-size: 10px;
  }

  h1 {
      font-size: 3rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 5rem;
  }
  
  .content {
      padding: 24px;
      font-size: 2rem;
  }
/*
  .selling-point {
      display: flex;
      gap: 8px;
      align-items: center;

      font-size: 24px;
  }

  .selling-point .icon {
     color: var(--text-subtle);
  }
*/

  .graphic {
      height: 146px;
      position: relative;
  }

  .discipline {
      position: absolute;
  }

  .discipline.design {
      top: 0;
      left: calc(50% - 32px);
  }

  .discipline.product {
      bottom: 0;
      left: 36%;
  }

  .discipline.engineer {
      bottom: 0;
      right: 33%;
  }

  .graphic > svg {
      position: absolute;
      top: 1.6rem;
      left: calc(50% - 50px);
  }

  .thoughts {
      display: flex;
      gap: 24px;
  }

  .thoughts a {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      padding: 8px 16px;
      border-radius: 3px;
      background: var(--background-alt);
      text-decoration: none;
  }
</style>

